Enum Builder.Stage

    public static enum Builder.Stage
extends java.lang.Enum<Builder.Stage>

    An indication of stage for bundles/features/repositories/kars/profiles.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      Boot
      Karaf runtime is in boot stage when it installs OSGi bundles using Karaf features.
      Installed
      Installed stage is just a space where bundles and features may be installed after starting Karaf runtime (e.g., using Karaf shell commands, JMX or UI).
      Startup
      Karaf runtime is in startup stage when it installs OSGi bundles into OSGi framework before passing this responsibility to FeaturesService.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Startup

        public static final Builder.Stage Startup
        Karaf runtime is in startup stage when it installs OSGi bundles into OSGi framework before passing this responsibility to FeaturesService. A list of bundles to install is defined in ${karaf.etc}/startup.properties.

      • Boot

        public static final Builder.Stage Boot
        Karaf runtime is in boot stage when it installs OSGi bundles using Karaf features. Features (and features XML repositories) are defined in ${karaf.etc}/org.apache.karaf.features.cfg. Repositories and features available in startup stage should be visible in boot stage as well, as this is the stage where term Karaf feature gets its meaning.

      • Installed

        public static final Builder.Stage Installed
        Installed stage is just a space where bundles and features may be installed after starting Karaf runtime (e.g., using Karaf shell commands, JMX or UI).
